@section How to add new tutorial

Tutorials are stored in the directory @file{tutorials}. Each
tutorial is by convention placed in a single directory named
@file{xx.name} wher xx is a two letter language code (for example 
@file{en.zqlzoo}).

To add the a tutorial to the database run SQL function
@code{init_tutorial} like

@example
SELECT sqltutor.init_tutorial('English', 'SQLzoo', 'en.sqlzoo');
@end example

@noindent where first two parameters define tutorial language and name (used in
the opening dialogue) and internal tutorial label.

To populate the new tutorial with questions you can use plain text
files in @file{quiz} format, that is converted to SQL by helper
program @file{quiz}.

@example
../.quiz/quiz en.sqlzoo $(QUIZ_FILES) | psql $(SQLTUTOR_DATABASE)
@end example

@noindent where first parameter is the tutorial label.

@section How to add new dataset

Datasets are organized similarly to tutorials in a directory
@file{tutorials} in separate subdirectories. After populating the
database with tutoral tables and data you run SQL function
@code{sqltutor.init_dataset('buses', 2008, 'http://sqlzoo.net/')} with
parameters tutorial name, year and data source. For each table the
function @code{sqltutor.add_ds_table('buses', 1, 'route', 'num,
company, pos, stop')"} where second parameter is the order in which
the table is listed in tutorial dialog, table name and list of
columns.

@noindent Example:

@example
psql $(SQLTUTOR_DATABASE) \
   -c "SELECT sqltutor.init_dataset('buses', 2008, 'http://sqlzoo.net/')"
psql $(SQLTUTOR_DATABASE) \
   -c "SELECT sqltutor.add_ds_table('buses', 1, 'stops',   'id, name')"
psql $(SQLTUTOR_DATABASE) \
   -c "SELECT sqltutor.add_ds_table('buses', 2, 'route',   \
                                    'num, company, pos, stop')"
@end example

